  "context_sent_to_llm": "\nDocument: PelicanDeliversInc_20200211_S-1_EX-10.3_11975895_EX-10.3_Development Agreement2 (1).pdf\nSection: Document Summary\nPage: 1\n\n**Comprehensive Summary of the Software Development Agreement**\n\n**Parties:**\n\n- **DOT COM LLC (Developer)**: A software development company responsible for designing, developing, and delivering software applications.\n- **Pelican Delivers Inc. (Client)**: A business entity that has engaged the Developer to create a software application.\n\n**Core Purpose of the Agreement:**\n\nThe Software Development Agreement outlines the terms and conditions for the performance of software design services and development between the Developer and the Client. The agreement details the scope of work, payment terms, intellectual property rights, and termination rules.\n\n**Key Obligations:**\n\n- **Developer Obligations:**\n  - Design, develop, and deliver the \"Pelican Delivers Application Phase 1\" and related services, work product, and documentation.\n  - Provide services, deliverables, and documentation to the Client upon designated milestones.\n  - Use best efforts to complete services and deliverables by the Final Delivery Date.\n  - Transfer all works to the Client upon termination of the agreement.\n- **Client Obligations:**\n  - Perform Acceptance Tests within designated time periods to determine if deliverables conform to the Service Order and Specifications.\n  - Notify the Developer in writing of any issues with a Milestone Deliverable within 10 days of its Acceptance Test Date.\n  - Pay the Developer's Fees, Expenses (if any), and Bonus via wire transfer to the Developer's bank account.\n  - Provide reasonable assistance to the Developer in completing the Services and producing the Deliverables.\n- **Mutual Obligations:**\n  - Both parties must maintain confidentiality and non-disclosure of confidential information.\n  - Both parties must refrain from making negative statements or posts about each other, their companies, employees, and affiliates online or offline.\n\n**Termination Rules:**\n\n- **Termination Without Cause:** Either party can terminate this Agreement with two weeks' written notice.\n- **Termination For Cause:** This Agreement can be terminated immediately by either party under certain conditions, including material breach, non-payment of undisputed fees, misappropriation of confidential information, or illegal activities.\n- **Obligations Upon Termination:** Upon termination of this Agreement or any Statement of Work (SOW), the Client must pay any outstanding fees, and the Developer will refund any non-accrued pre-paid fees. The Developer will also provide up to three (3) months of Termination Assistance Services, including knowledge transfer and data migration, at an additional cost to the Client.\n\n**Other Key Provisions:**\n\n- **Intellectual Property Rights:** The Developer assigns and transfers all copyright and intellectual property ownership in the Works to the Client.\n- **Payment Terms:** The Client is required to pay the Developer's Fees, Expenses (if any), and Bonus via wire transfer to the Developer's bank account.\n- **Dispute Resolution:** This Agreement is governed by Washington state law, and the parties must attempt friendly negotiations and mediation to resolve disputes, with the option to proceed to state and federal courts in King County, Washington if necessary.\n",
  "generated_answer": "Based on the provided context, here are the critical points and key highlights:\n\n* **Parties Involved:**\n  * DOT COM LLC (Developer)\n  * Pelican Delivers Inc. (Client)\n* **Core Purpose of the Agreement:**\n  * Outline the terms and conditions for the performance of software design services and development between the Developer and the Client.\n* **Key Obligations:**\n  * Developer Obligations:\n    + Design, develop, and deliver the \"Pelican Delivers Application Phase 1\" and related services, work product, and documentation.\n    + Transfer all works to the Client upon termination of the agreement.\n  * Client Obligations:\n    + Perform Acceptance Tests within designated time periods.\n    + Pay the Developer's Fees, Expenses (if any), and Bonus via wire transfer.\n  * Mutual Obligations:\n    + Maintain confidentiality and non-disclosure of confidential information.\n    + Refrain from making negative statements or posts about each other, their companies, employees, and affiliates online or offline.\n* **Termination Rules:**\n  * Termination Without Cause: Either party can terminate this Agreement with two weeks' written notice.\n  * Termination For Cause: This Agreement can be terminated immediately by either party under certain conditions.\n* **Other Key Provisions:**\n  * Intellectual Property Rights: The Developer assigns and transfers all copyright and intellectual property ownership in the Works to the Client.\n  * Payment Terms: The Client is required to pay the Developer's Fees, Expenses (if any), and Bonus via wire transfer.\n  * Dispute Resolution: This Agreement is governed by Washington state law, and the parties must attempt friendly negotiations and mediation to resolve disputes.",
